<i>noun</i>: 해소 [해ː소], 완화 [완ː화], 안심 [안심], 안도 [안도], 구호품 [구ː호품], 구호물자 [구ː호물짜], 구호 [구ː호], 구제 [구ː제], 구원 [구ː원], 구급 [구ː급], 교대 [교대] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>해소 [해ː소]</dt><br>
<dd>1. resolution; relief; easing; release</dd><br>
<dd>어려운 일이나 좋지 않은 상태를 해결하여 없애 버림.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of addressing and getting rid of a difficult problem or unfavorable situation.</dd><br>
<dd>2. breakup; dissolution</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 단체나 조직 등을 없애 버림.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of breaking up a certain group or organization and making it disappear.</dd><br>
<dt>완화 [완ː화]</dt><br>
<dd>1. relaxation; easing</dd><br>
<dd>긴장된 상태나 매우 급한 것을 느슨하게 함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of relaxing something tense or stressful.</dd><br>
<dd>2. relief; alleviation</dd><br>
<dd>병의 증상이 약해짐.</dd><br>
<dd>For the symptoms of a disease to be assuaged.</dd><br>
<dt>안심 [안심]</dt><br>
<dd>relief; peace of mind; assurance</dd><br>
<dd>걱정 없이 마음을 편히 가짐.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of one's peaceful mind, without worries.</dd><br>
<dt>안도 [안도]</dt><br>
<dd>1. resting place; refuge; rest</dd><br>
<dd>사는 곳에서 평안하게 잘 지냄. 또는 평안히 지낼 수 있는 곳.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of living peacefully in one's dwelling; a place where one can stay peacefully.</dd><br>
<dd>2. relief</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일이 잘되어 마음을 놓음.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of feeling relieved because something has turned out well.</dd><br>
<dt>구호품 [구ː호품]</dt><br>
<dd>relief; aid</dd><br>
<dd>재난이나 재해를 당한 사람을 돕기 위한 물품.</dd><br>
<dd>Goods handed out to the victims of a disaster or calamity to help them.</dd><br>
<dt>구호물자 [구ː호물짜]</dt><br>
<dd>relief; aid</dd><br>
<dd>재난이나 재해를 당한 사람을 돕는 데 필요한 물품.</dd><br>
<dd>Goods handed out to the victims of a disaster or calamity to help them.</dd><br>
<dt>구호 [구ː호]</dt><br>
<dd>1. relief; aid</dd><br>
<dd>재난이나 재해를 당한 사람을 도와서 보호함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of helping and protecting the victims of a disaster or calamity.</dd><br>
<dd>2. taking care; attending; nursing</dd><br>
<dd>병이 들거나 다친 사람을 간호함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of looking after the sick or injured.</dd><br>
<dt>구제 [구ː제]</dt><br>
<dd>help; relief; aid</dd><br>
<dd>어려운 처지에 놓인 사람을 도와줌.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of helping a person in a difficult situation.</dd><br>
<dt>구원 [구ː원]</dt><br>
<dd>1. rescue; relief</dd><br>
<dd>어려움이나 위험에 빠진 사람이나 단체 등을 구해 줌.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of saving individuals, groups, etc., from a difficult situation or danger.</dd><br>
<dd>2. salvation</dd><br>
<dd>기독교에서, 인간을 죄악과 죽음에서 구하는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>In Christianity, the act of saving people from their sins and death.</dd><br>
<dt>구급 [구ː급]</dt><br>
<dd>1. relief; rescue</dd><br>
<dd>위급한 상황에서 구하여 냄.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of saving someone or something from an emergency situation.</dd><br>
<dd>2. first-aid</dd><br>
<dd>생명이 위급한 환자나 부상자에게 우선 목숨을 구하기 위한 처치를 하여 그 고비를 넘기게 하는 것.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of treating a critically ill patient or injured person to save his/her life, and helping him/her recover.</dd><br>
<dt>교대 [교대]</dt><br>
<dd>1. rotation; shift</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일을 여러 사람이 나누어서 차례를 바꾸어 가며 함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of assuming or taking on certain tasks in a particular order by dividing them among various persons.</dd><br>
<dd>2. relief</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일을 여럿이 나누어서 차례에 따라 맡아서 하는 사람.</dd><br>
<dd>A person who, in turn, assumes a certain task when such work is divided among various persons.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>